 Nanu Dahal, 37, a Nepalese national wanted by Delhi police in a forgery case, was arrested at Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport on Tuesday morning. Delhi police had issued a look-out notice for the woman. Dahal was about to board a Bangkok-bound flight when she was intercepted by immigration officials. 

 Power supply to the Topsia Road, Chowbhaga Road, Tiljala Road, Tiljala Shibtala Lane and Mahendra Roy Lane areas and both sides of the Park Circus EM Bypass connector may be affected from 9 am to 1 pm on Wednesday due to repairs.

 Anjali Khara, 55, was critically injured when a private bus on route 30B knocked her down in front of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation headquarters on SN Banerjee Road on Monday evening. Police said Khara was trying to cross the road. She was admitted to Medical College and Hospital. The driver was arrested.

 Birju Gurung, 28, a CTC guard, died after being hit by a car on AJC Bose Road, near Mullickbazar, late on Monday. Police said he was taken to NRS Medical College and Hospital where he died. The driver was arrested.

 An Exhibition Special train, depicting the history of insurance in India and the schemes on offer, arrived at Howrah station on Tuesday. The exhibition is being organised by the Life Insurance Corporation. The train began its journey from Safdarjung station near Delhi on April 26. 

